{
  "texts": [
    "This justifies their use in developing ultraviolet completions of the RL predictions.The results in Ref.",
    "[26] were obtained using algebraic Ansätze for pion and kaon generalised parton distributions (GPDs), constrained entirely by hadron-scale π and K valence-parton DFs.",
    "Owing to the D-term ambiguity [82] encountered, e.g., in connecting GPDs with gravitational form factors, reliable results for θ P 1 (0) could not be obtained in Ref.",
    "Herein, there is no D-term ambiguity: as already seen for the pion, the RL truncation supplies a definite prediction for θ P 1 (t).",
    "The CSM predictions for kaon elastic electromagnetic and gravitational form factors are drawn in Figs. 2B and 3."
  ]
}